    • Constructor Detail

      • FailedInternetConnectionException

        public FailedInternetConnectionException​(java.lang.String cardNumStr)
        Constructs a new exception that occurs when the Internet connection is not available when trying to access the TeleChargeAndPay remote system with a valid card number, but prior to being able to check if the intended order would be accepted or not by the remote system. The order is not completed, and the caller may decide whether or not it wants to retry (on its own) this operation.
        Parameters:
        cardNumStr - The cardNumStr The string card number involved in the exception
